runs.comm: starts with a lifter right at the left-hander's chest, he is surprised and fends it down on to the pitch
plenty of width given on this length ball slanted across, and he steps forward to scythe it past cover
in the gap again, superb timing, this length ball was on a tighter line, but he opened the face and ran it between backward point and cover, the ball raced away
straight length ball directed couple of feet down the leg side
corrects the line with a length ball on off and middle, he taps it towards extra cover
beaten, as he wafts at a widish back of a length ball
third man is up, this is wide again, and he this time he steers it nicely past the man in the circle
length ball on the pad, turned to midwicket for a single
rides the bounce on this short of a length ball and runs it behind point
stretches across to play out a length ball to point
this is fuller, he's backed away, cleared front leg and mowed it way over the long on boundary
angles it across on a fullish length, he comes forward to push to covers
guides a short of a length ball to backward point
width as he slants it across, third man is up, and it has been guided neatly in the gap
floats it up on off stump, pushed to midwicket
wobbles in a bit and bounces as he pitches it up, he stabs it square on the leg side off a thick inside edge
taps it in front of extra cover and rushes for the single
yorker, around off, he digs it out to point
slanted in middle and leg, turned square, where the man in the ring cannot stop it
bowled full into the pad, and it is clipped through midwicket, there is a man in the deep there
chopped on, went to cut a shortish ball that was not wide, and the thick inside edge clattered into the stumps
goes back to a short of a length ball and defends
beaten, was stuck on the crease, this was pitched fuller, and he goes walking looking to defend
nicely across and behind the line of this length ball
overpitched, and he has attacked this, forcing it into the gap between point and cover
holds the line after being angled in from round the stumps, defended
saw him backing away early and got it right up in the blockhole on middle, he just got the bat down in time

good take from third man running back towards the boundary, slower length ball just outside off, he makes some room again and has a heave, thick edge swirls high, but van der Gugten has judged this superbly
full delivery driven to extra cover
drives this length ball on the up from the crease, to covers
away to backward point, and that is a wicket-maiden
shortish and sharp, he is pinned back into the crease and plays it out to point
short of a length, angled in, turned to midwicket
that reared at him from back of a length, he took his eyes off the ball, and fended at it with one hand on the bat, edged it fine fortunately
dug in short and he is awkward again, but this is angled down the leg side
nice response, rising again, but outside off now, and he is in the air as he punches it over backward point
has a go at the pull but is beaten as this rises and also holds the line
he was looking for the punch through the off side again, but this cut in and he had to check the stroke
sits up from a shortish length, some turn there, pulled to wide long on
tossed up ball around off, hit to long on
pulls but mistimes it down the track, and bowler stops it with a dive
comes forward to defend a tossed up ball
nudges it off the pad to vacant midwicket, RVDM after it
hops, opens the face, and runs a short of a length ball to third man
hooks a short ball that comes slowly off the pitch, to deep square leg
short and wide, cut hard, straight to the sweeper
opens the face to run a widish ball to third man
wants to pull but is hurried in to the shot and the ball rolls on to the pitch
he is in the air again as he goes hard at a short ball outside off, upper cuts it high over point, given as four after a look at replays
length ball worked to long on
turn there, beats him on an uncertain forward push, he was looking to push it to leg
and beaten again, this time by lot more flight and turn, he moved inside the line wanting to drive with the turn, keeper cannot collect it, that bounced too
backs away and cuts a flatter one to the sweeper
comes forward to defend to extra cover
turns an angled fullish ball through midwicket
length ball from the left-armer, turned square to leg
straightish ball with some flight, tapped to the off side
carries straight on around middle, guided to point
fuller ball, he reverse sweeps, Swart at short third after it, dives near the rope, and somehow keeps it in
widish length ball, worked through midwicket
tossed up full outside off, slog-swept to deep midwicket
short and wide, steered to third man
overpitched outside off, driven to the sweeper
short and wide again, he edges the cut fine to third man, fielder slides across to cut it off
almost a yorker, stabbed towards vacant midwicket, captain runs after it, keeps them to one
low full toss on the pad, flicked to deep square
tosses it up across the right hander, who prods at it, is beaten
opens up to pull it between deep midwicket and long on
not too short, but he goes to leg to pull again, to wide long on
tossed up on off, defended
dropped, wanted to pull, this was slanted wide, he toe ends it back to the bowler, a high chance, over his head, it hits his fingers and bursts away
wide long off takes it, he forced it from the crease, looking to go over extra cover, but the man in the deep had it covered with a short run
full outside off, turned to wide long on
sharp short ball, he moves across, and keeps bat close to himself to let it pass
walks across to a short of a length ball outside off and almost plays on with a thick inside edge
pushes off the front foot, straight to point, not getting the single
comes in from a length outside off, is worked in front of square
slower short ball does not get up much, he misses the pull, and the ball carries to the keeper off the pad, has that taken an edge, no, says umpire Kulkarni
he has hardly turned the ball, but has varied his lines, this is widish, and he cannot get hold of the pull
and this one has turned a bit, the line is much tighter, right on middle and leg, Patil wants to reverse sweep, misses, and has leg stump rattled
spins away after starting wide to the left hander, he stretches for a cut, is beaten
length ball pushed quietly past slip
now he is turning it, tosses it up on off, he plays it out from the crease
straightish and flat, cut straight to cover
tossed up ball full, driven to extra cover
flatter and quicker, cut neatly, not wide enough of backward point
flighted yorker outside off, he tries to run it fine, misses
slanted in to the pad, deep midwicket runs in quickly and keeps them to one
craps him with a length ball on middle and leg, turned to midwicket
sweeps a pretty full one, underedges it to short fine leg
full on middle, pushed down to long on
goes hard at a pitched up ball, hits it along the ground to long off
back of a length, slanted in a bit, he uses that and whips it behind square, fine leg runs around and keeps it in
turned off the pad behind square
first boundary in nearly eight overs, overpitched outside off, and he drills it past a diving point
two in two, flays again outside off, and a thick edge flies past the keeper
mishits a sweep off this low full toss, in front of square
almost hit leg stump, he walked across looking to heave it square, missed the tossed up delivery which just went down leg
goes down on his knee for an almighty slog sweep but does not connect again
this time he connects on the slog-sweep, and sends it sailing comfortably into the lap of deep square leg
two in two for RVDM, batsman clears front leg and has a slog at a tossed up ball, which sneaks in under and hits middle stump
almost a yorker, pushed back, RVDM dives to his left to stop it
wants to get under the ball, but is slightly short of a length and he has to turn it to midwicket
jumps out to another back of a length ball, hits it to long off
steps out and has a go, does not get much timing on it, and the ball travels slowly to long off
this one will go, overpitched on the pad, he gets front foot out of the way, and gets under it to lift it straight over the bowler
slogs a length ball to long on
backs away to leg and heaves, gets an underedge in front of square
gets it in the blockhole outside off, and a drive and miss results
swings in a bit, full length, drilled on the bounce to extra cover
slogs a back of a length ball on the bounce to long on now
wants to cart a full one over midwicket, but is beaten as it travels just past leg
full and wide, he gets enough bat on it as he stretches to hammer it behind point, third man runs hard and dives, in vain
short of a length ball, he backs away and edges a slog towards long off
makes lots of room outside leg, bowler follows him, a thick inside edge goes to square leg
bends his knee and slogs it to deep square leg
one-handed beauty from Borren, length ball is heaved over midwicket, Borren trots backwards and sticks out his right hand to snap up the ball
cannot get away a full delivery and will take the leg bye
on a knee and swings hard, is hit on the leg
and they fail to put bat to ball for the last time in the innings, back of a length ball hits thigh pad
